# Cleanup of one-shot scaffolding
# (see commit titled "chore(scripts): remove one-shot migration scaffolding").
#
# The six scripts/ entries below were migration glue for two broken-revert
# incidents earlier in this project (Phase 8 hint revert + the duplicate-
# brace recovery). They were never tracked by git, so a plain `git commit`
# against them produces no diff -- git only records changes to tracked
# files. Recording them in .gitignore is the actually-enforced mechanism
# that prevents their filenames from quietly re-entering the working tree.
scripts/finish_reapply.py
scripts/patch_main_apply.py
scripts/reapply_dispatch_and_sweep.py
scripts/revert_hint_experiment.py
scripts/run-bench-backSweep.sh
scripts/run-bench-dispatch.sh
